==English==

===Etymology===
Canadian, 1945. Backformed from ''[[supercharge]]'' and ''[[up]]'' as '''suped-up''', modified by mis-hearing to the more common '''souped-up'''. - [[w:Eric Partridge]], ''A Dictionary of Slang''

===Adjective===
'''souped-up''', ''also'' '''[[suped-up]]'''
# ''(of a motor vehicle):'' modified for higher performance, applied by extension to other items

